headline: Workday Stock Soars as Forecasts Ease ‘Wall of Worry’ Over Outlook
summary: Shares of  Workday  were gaining after the software company turned in quarterly results and financial guidance that pleased Wall Street.  Workday stock increased 7% to $273.18 and is on track for its largest daily percentage increase since August when the company turned in solid quarterly results, according to Dow Jones Market Data.  The company reported fourth-quarter adjusted earnings of $1.92 per share after the market closed on Tuesday, beating the consensus call for $1.78 among analysts tracked by FactSet.
